    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>An Old-Fashioned Idea</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Incoming: An Old-Fas</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Your Car Can Double as a Paid Advertisement'' (News Watch, Aug. 3) said that a company called AutoWraps was putting paid advertisements on privately owned autos. About 30 years ago, Kool cigarettes did that on at least a couple of hundred Volkswagen Beetles in the New York City area. They were paid monthly, and the contract included a provision for re-painting when the contract ended. It was common in those early years to see a Volkswagen with the ghost of the Kool logo visible through the paint job.</p>
        <p>IRWIN FRIEDMAN  Queens</p>
      </block>
